}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 109.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Either in December 1310 at Vercelli or in January 1311 at Milano, Dante was \softline
apparently presented to the new emperor, Henry VII (see Frugoni's notes in his edition of Dante's \softline
}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Epistles}{\plain \fs24 \f1 , p. 564).  Dante himself reports that he embraced the emperor's feet (}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Epistle}{\plain \fs24 \f1  VII.9).  It is \softline
