}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 111.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Dante's threefold beating of his chest has been glossed, since the time of the Ottimo \softline
(comm. to vv. 106-111), as signifying 'mea culpa, mea culpa, mea maxima culpa.'  Andrea Lancia \softline
