}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 117-126.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Sensible allegorical expositions of the two keys are found variously, but of \softline
particular use is Poletto's gloss (to vv. 115-117).  The golden key denotes the authority to absolve \softline
